The paper discusses the challenges of blockage in mmWave bands and its impact on various aspects of the protocol stack, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also presents a novel spatial dynamic channel sounding system based on phased array transmitters and receivers operating at 60 GHz, which falls under the domain of multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the open issues towards developing statistical dynamic models, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation (cs.PE).
